Wokha is a Town and a municipality in the state of Nagaland, India.It is the headquarters of its namesake district(see wokha district). It is located at a distance of about 75 km from the state capital Kohima.
&nbsp;
Wokha literally means "head count" or "census" in Lotha language

Kiphire is a small town, situated at an elevation of 896 m (2,940 ft) above sea level and is the headquarters of Kiphire district. Kiphire is about 254 km from Kohima, the capital of Nagaland.
&nbsp;
